gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Bucks 129, Warriors 118
gameRecap.excerpt: The Bucks defeated the Warriors, 129-118. Giannis Antetokounmpo led the Bucks with 33 points, nine rebounds, and five assists as Damian Lillard (27 points, six rebounds, seven assists) and Khris Middleton (24 points, 10 assists) totaled 51 points. Jonathan Kuminga had a career-high 28 points as Brandon Podziemski (23 points, 10 rebounds) and Klay Thompson (21 points) totaled 44 points. Milwaukee improves to 27-12 as the Warriors move to 18-21.
